{"answer":"Yes, Magnolia Gardens is in compliance with Chapter 276 of Title 26 of the Texas Administrative Code regarding the pet deposit charged for the emotional support animal.

The regulation (in the resident contracting rules) states: "pet deposit. A pet deposit does not apply to service animals. A service animal is any guide dog, signal dog, or other animal trained to provide assistance to an individual with a disability."

This is the only provision addressing pet deposits or animals in the chapter. It exempts only trained service animals; emotional support animals do not qualify under the definition. No other rules prohibit the deposit for ESAs. Mr. Johns (a DHS client) was charged only for his ESA, so the facility's action complies. (Note the separate rule against security/damage deposits for DHS clients does not apply to pet deposits.)","status":"completed"}
